            "title": "The Private Prison Project",
            "slug": "the-private-prison-project",
            "summary": "For-profit detention continues to reap the rewards of an incarceration system filled to the brim and facing an uncertain future.\r\n\r\nOur FOIA requests have released thousands of documents that show how for-profit prisons have leveraged the legal system to their advantage, letting companies pick-and-choose inmates to off-load costs, ignore complaints and concerns, and create dangerous conditions for prisoners and staff alike.\r\n\r\nThis is all done while billions of taxpayer dollars are funneled into these private companies, which then pour millions into politicians' campaigns to keep their growth going.\r\n\r\nWith your help, we can provide needed scrutiny of an industry few are even aware exists.",
            "description": "The private correctional industry as we now see it grew out of eighties privatization fervor. Like so many corporate promises, the prospect of a quick fix has gotten many a government “partner” to sign on.\r\n\r\nOver two-thirds of immigrant detention facilities are privately-managed. A steady number of state and local facilities are also under contract with for-profit operators. And, though the privatization of prisons has been controversial for decades, the current administration is poised to expand the industry.\r\n\r\nWant to learn more about how we got here? Want to stay on top of where it's going? Check out our previous articles and sign up for our mailing list.\r\n\r\n# LEARN MORE\r\n*Delve into the dirty details of corporate corrections.*\r\n\r\nBrowse through our archive of stories and public records requests to learn more about the history of private prisons, new developments, and other facts about one of the most secretive industries in operation today.\r\n\r\n**[Five myths of the private prison industry](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2015/oct/19/5-myths-private-prison-industry/)**\r\n\r\n**[Five concerns about private prisons from the ‘80s that are still valid today](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jan/13/5-concerns-private-prisons/)**\r\n\r\n**[Five ways private prisons break the rules - and get away with it](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2017/jul/25/five-ways-private-prisons-break-rules/)**\r\n\r\n# HOW CAN YOU HELP?\r\n*Whether you want to donate dollars, thoughts, or feedback, we're happy to have you here and interested.*\r\n\r\n**[Five ways to contribute to the private prison project.](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2018/jul/25/ppp-five-ways/)**\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.muckrock.com/assignment/private-prison-feedback-line-43/embed/\" width=\"100%\" height=\"600px\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n# THE PRIVATE PRISON PRIMER\r\n*Learn more about the growth and maintenance of private interests sustained by bodies under lock and key.*\r\n\r\n**How is this even legal?** - [Part One](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jan/26/how-are-private-prisons-even-legal-part-i/) and [Part Two](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jan/28/private-prison-primer-how-even-legal-part-2/)\r\n\r\n**Who regulates this?** - [Part One](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/feb/23/makes-dollars-does-it-make-sense/) and [Part Two](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/feb/25/makes-dollars-does-it-make-sense-2/)\r\n\r\n**Stolen shoes and the Kingman riots** - [Part One](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jun/14/private-prison-primer-grievances-1/) and [Part Two](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jun/16/private-prison-primer-grievances-2/)\r\n\r\n**A tale of two prison towns** - [Part One](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/may/10/tale-two-prisons-part-1-prison-city-usa/) and [Part Two](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/may/12/private-prison-primer-tale-two-prison-towns-part-2/)\r\n\r\n**At what cost?** - [Part One](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jul/19/private-prison-primer-what-cost-part-1/) and [Part Two](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/jul/21/private-prison-primer-what-cost-part-2/)\r\n\r\n**What are we really signing on for?** - [Part One](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/apr/05/private-prison-primer-what-are-we-really-signing/), [Part Two](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/apr/07/private-prison-primer-what-are-we-really-signing-p/), [Part Three](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/apr/12/what-are-we-really-signing-3/), and [Part Four](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/apr/14/what-are-we-really-signing-4/)\r\n\r\n**[All prisons are private prisons](https://www.muckrock.com/news/archives/2016/aug/18/all-prisons-are-private-prisons-ii/).**",
